<p class="courseblockdesc">
Introduction to design process: ideation and iteration. Emphasis on understanding design through physical investigations utilizing specific fabrication materials and methods for prototype and critique. Course Information: Extensive computer use required. Prerequisite(s): <a href="/search/?P=DES%20140" title="DES&#160;140" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'DES 140');">DES&#160;140</a> and <a href="/search/?P=DES%20150" title="DES&#160;150" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'DES 150');">DES&#160;150</a> and <a href="/search/?P=DES%20160" title="DES&#160;160" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'DES 160');">DES&#160;160</a> and <a href="/search/?P=DES%20170" title="DES&#160;170" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'DES 170');">DES&#160;170</a>. Corequisites: Requires concurrent registration in <a href="/search/?P=DES%20208" title="DES&#160;208" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'DES 208');">DES&#160;208</a>, <a href="/search/?P=DES%20222" title="DES&#160;222" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'DES 222');">DES&#160;222</a>.<br />
