<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>DES&#160;318.  Typography III: Expression.  4 hours.</strong></p>
<p class="courseblockdesc">
Textual investigations of typographic form of expression with an emphasis on composition (contrast, rhythm, tension), non-linearity, visual argumentation, dimensions, and the interplay between digital and analog operations. Course Information: Previously listed as AD 315. Extensive computer use required. Prerequisite(s): <a href="/search/?P=DES%20209" title="DES&#160;209" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'DES 209');">DES&#160;209</a>. Class Schedule Information: To be properly registered, students must enroll in one Lecture and one Laboratory.<br />
